    {
      "type": "heading",
      "data": {
        "size": 1,
        "content": "Using SCSS with Nuxt"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "data": {
        "quote": false,
        "children": [
          {
            "content": "To use SCSS with Nuxt, you need to add the",
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "code": false,
            "link": ""
          },
          {
            "content": "sass",
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "code": true,
            "link": ""
          },
          {
            "content": "package to your project. You can do this by running the following command:",
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "code": false,
            "link": ""
          },
          {
            "content": "pnpm add -D sass",
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "code": true,
            "link": ""
          },
          {
            "content": "(works completely fine with a",
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "code": false,
            "link": ""
          },
          {
            "content": "tauri app",
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "code": false,
            "link": "https://tauri.app/"
          },
          {
            "content": ")",
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "code": false,
            "link": ""
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "data": {
        "quote": false,
        "children": [
          {
            "content": "After adding the package, you can use Sass in your Nuxt project by changing the",
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "code": false,
            "link": ""
          },
          {
            "content": "<style>",
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "code": true,
            "link": ""
          },
          {
            "content": "tags to",
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "code": false,
            "link": ""
          },
          {
            "content": "<style lang=\"scss\">",
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "code": true,
            "link": ""
          },
          {
            "content": "tags in all .vue files.",
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "code": false,
            "link": ""
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "data": {
        "size": 1,
        "content": "Using SCSS with HTML in VS Code"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "data": {
        "quote": false,
        "children": [
          {
            "content": "To use SCSS with HTML in VS Code, you need to install the",
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "code": false,
            "link": ""
          },
          {
            "content": "glenn2223.live-sass",
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "code": true,
            "link": ""
          },
          {
            "content": "extension. After installing the extension, open any",
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "code": false,
            "link": ""
          },
          {
            "content": ".scss",
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "code": true,
            "link": ""
          },
          {
            "content": "file and click on the",
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "code": false,
            "link": ""
          },
          {
            "content": "watch sass",
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "code": true,
            "link": ""
          },
          {
            "content": "button at the bottom right of the screen.",
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "code": false,
            "link": ""
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "data": {
        "quote": false,
        "children": [
          {
            "content": "To import the generated CSS into your HTML file, use the same method as you would for normal CSS. However, make sure to use the",
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "code": false,
            "link": ""
          },
          {
            "content": ".css",
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "code": true,
            "link": ""
          },
          {
            "content": "file extension instead of",
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "code": false,
            "link": ""
          },
          {
            "content": ".scss",
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "code": true,
            "link": ""
          },
          {
            "content": ", as",
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "code": false,
            "link": ""
          },
          {
            "content": "live-sass",
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "code": true,
            "link": ""
          },
          {
            "content": "will convert",
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "code": false,
            "link": ""
          },
          {
            "content": ".scss",
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "code": true,
            "link": ""
          },
          {
            "content": "files to",
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "code": false,
            "link": ""
          },
          {
            "content": ".css",
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "code": true,
            "link": ""
          },
          {
            "content": "files.",
            "bold": false,
            "italic": false,
            "code": false,
            "link": ""
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ]
}